      <h>temporal bounding</h>
      <p>When <g>gu</g>
        <en>until, till</en> governs a noun expression which can be interpreted as identifying a
        point in time, it introduces a <emph>bounding</emph> adverbial, converting an imperfective
        situation into a perfective one with a specified termination point – <ul>
          <li>Bidh Raonaid ann an Lunnainn <m>gu Disathairne</m>. <en>Rachel will be in London till
              Saturday.</en>
          </li>
          <li>Shnàmh e anns an abhainn <m>gu meadhan latha</m>. <en>He swam in the river until
